25|$|The Eastern {{religions}} are <b>the</b> <b>religions</b> {{originating in the}} Eastern world— East, South and Southeast Asia —and thus having dissimilarities with Western religions. This includes the East Asian (namely Taoism and Confucianism) and Indian (namely Hinduism and Buddhism) religious traditions, historical Indo-Iranian religion such as Zoroastrianism (now practiced mostly in India) as well as animistic indigenous religions.|$|E
