5000|$|<b>The</b> Coconut <b>Religion</b> (Vietnamese: Đạo Dừa or Hòa đồng Tôn giáo) is a now-discontinued {{religion}} {{indigenous to}} southern Vietnam's [...] "Coconut Kingdom", {{where it was}} founded in 1963. <b>The</b> <b>religion</b> is largely based on some Buddhist and Christian beliefs, alongside the teachings of founder Nguyễn Thành Nam, a Vietnamese scholar. <b>The</b> <b>religion</b> was abolished by Vietnamese authorities in 1975. At its peak, <b>the</b> <b>religion</b> had some 4,000 followers.|$|R
